5. Websockets URI - /wsserver/login
to login to the websocket server the http POST request should set a cookie in the request header

cookie name should be "whirlpool"
cookie value should be our usual jwt token that is received after a successful login with user id and password. 

POST request should have the following - 

user = loginId
password = jwt token

loginId is the loginId used to login to the dashboard. 

if response is success then send upgrade request to below end-point, header should be set to "Upgrade" and value should be "websocket"

"ws://" + "api.streetone.com" + "/wsserver/wsupgrade"

websocket handshake should be complete now. the following websocket frames will be streamed to the client - 

"order-stream"
"order-exec-stream" 
"trade-alert-stream" 
"security-quote-stream"
"ats-quote-stream" 

