7. Market Status
	1. display a horizontal bar with three input text boxes arranged horizontally. 

		1. Label for text box 1 should be "User Number", inside the text box display "Enter user number". next to the text box display a button labelled "Halt" 
		2. Label for text box 2 should be "Symbol", inside the text box display "Enter symbol". next to the text box display a button labelled "Halt" 
		3. Label for text box 2 should be "Market", inside the text box display "Enter market". next to the text box display a button labelled "Halt" 

	when the user presses the "Halt" button above, then POST to the below end-point

	/marketstatus

	flag - value should be 1
	trade - value should be the string the user entered in any of the above text box

	2. below the horizontal bar display "Trading Stopped", 

	3. below "Trading Stopped" display the GET response from below end-point. response is a list of marketStatus

	   /marketstatus

	   each line should display string contained in trade and next to it a button labelled "Resume Trading"

	   when user clicks on "Resume Trading" button then POST to the below end-point 

	   /marketstatus

	   flag - value should be 0
	   trade - value should be string contained in trade

